# clangd LSP config (https://clangd.llvm.org/config).
#
# The per-TU source of truth for compile flags is the compile_commands.json each CMake build emits
# (-DCMAKE_EXPORT_COMPILE_COMMANDS=ON, set in cpp/CMakeLists.txt and throughput-lab/cpp/CMakeLists.txt).
# clangd auto-discovers that DB in each project's build/ subdir (cpp/build, throughput-lab/cpp/build),
# so it resolves every .cpp — and every header reachable from an indexed .cpp — with the real -std and
# -I flags. Include paths live ONLY in the DB (no hand-duplicated, drift-prone copy here — the SSOT).
#
# This file adds ONE thing the DB cannot: a -std FLOOR for a header opened in isolation before any
# including TU is parsed. Without it clangd defaults to an older C++ standard and reports std::span /
# std::expected as nonexistent (the dominant false-error source across this C++23 codebase).
#
# NOTE for the throughput-lab: its DB only carries the chocofarm/include path when configured with
# -DTLAB_REAL_GENERATOR=ON (that option adds the dir). Configure with it ON for the real_gen_* files.
CompileFlags:
  Add: [-std=c++23]
